<item>
            <title>[LU-1417] lov_exit and osc_exit called lu_device_type_fini()  twice</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1417</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;lov_exit and osc_exit explicitly called lu_device_type_fini() right before calling class_unregister_type(), however, class_unregister_type() will call lu_device_type_fini() too, which means lov_device_type and osc_device_type will be finalized twice, and those lu_context_keys in these two modules will be degistered twice too.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We never saw any complaint about this is because lu_context_key_degister() will silently ignore unregistered key.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
